## Description
Due to the nature of the regular expressions responsible for parsing and sanitizing commenting text blocks, leading whitespace, hyphens, and pipe characters are removed when rendering Swagger output, making Markdown tables and bulleted lists (not to mention nested ones) unusable in documentation. Example:
```go
// - bullet point 1
// - bullet point 2
// | col1 | col2 |
// |------|------|
// | val1 | val2 |
```
is being rendered as
```
bullet point 1
bullet point 2
col1 | col2 |
------|------|
 val1 | val2 |
```

Now, on a closer look at the code it appears that the pipe character is supposed to be used to mark pre-formatted text, so if we wrote the example as
```go
// |- bullet point 1
// |- bullet point 2
// || col1 | col2 |
// ||------|------|
// || val1 | val2 |
```
then the rendered output would be correctly formatted.

This approach seems brittle (apart from being undocumented) and unnecessary. We could simply determine the minimum indentation of the individual text blocks and unindent accordingly. I already implemented this feature in a local fork and will link the PR to this issue.

Note that this might break clients relying on the special `|` formatting approach.
